title: Kate Middleton and Prince William will tour overseas in 2016, their children are unlike to come
text:
Tweet 
There have been rumors that the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge are set to make a Caribbean tour next year. 
According to a royal source cited by HELLO! magazine, Kate Middleton and Prince William are scheduled to tour overseas, but the location is still unknown. 
Their children, Princess Charlotte, 4 months old, and Prince George, 2 years old, might not accompany them. 
“It was a one-off to take George to Australia and New Zealand last year and it is looking highly unlikely they will take their children with them on their next tour,” the Palace source told the publication. “We are looking at either spring or autumn, but have not ruled out the possibility of them doing both.” 
The news that William and Kate are set for a Caribbean tour next year was reported by the Daily Mail last month. 
“We are aware of the report about the Caribbean, but the location is yet to be decided,” the source also said. 
Back in August, People magazine reported that the Duke and Duchess are set for another royal tour in 2016, but their two adorable children won’t join them. 
Prince George already stole the show in 2014 when he visited New Zealand and Australia with his parents. Spread the rumor
